  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Prevention Strategies:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- International information sharing\n- Strict penalties for non-compliance\n\n4. Regulatory Mechanisms:\n- Financial institutions must implement compliance programs\n- Regular audits and inspections\n- Mandatory reporting of large or suspicious transactions\n- Sanctions for money laundering activities\n\n5. Enforcement:\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Intergovernmental cooperation\n- Prosecution of money laundering offenses\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
